# AWS Billing Audit — MRI Dev Environment

> **Date**: 2026-03-02 | **Region**: `ap-south-1` (Mumbai) | **RDS Status**: Paused

## Summary

Even with RDS paused, you have **several resources still actively billing**. The biggest cost driver right now is the **NAT Gateway + Elastic IP** combo.

---

## 💰 Active Billable Resources

| # | Resource | Type / Details | Estimated Monthly Cost | Status |
|---|----------|---------------|----------------------|--------|
| 1 | **NAT Gateway** | `mri-dev-nat` | **~$32–35/mo** (hourly charge + data) | 🔴 **Actively billing** |
| 2 | **Elastic IP** | `mri-dev-nat-eip` (attached to NAT GW) | ~$3.60/mo (free when attached to running instance, but NAT GW charges separately) | 🟡 Billing via NAT GW |
| 3 | **EC2 Bastion** | `mri-dev-bastion` · `t3.micro` | **~$7–8/mo** (or free if under Free Tier) | 🔴 **Running 24/7** |
| 4 | **RDS PostgreSQL** | `mri-dev-db` · `db.t3.micro` · 20GB gp2 | **~$0** while paused (storage: ~$2.30/mo) | 🟢 Paused (auto-resumes after 7 days!) |
| 5 | **S3 Bucket** | `mri-dev-outputs-{account_id}` · versioned | **~$0.01–0.50/mo** (depends on data stored) | 🟢 Minimal cost |
